---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '@/index.css';

const currentDate = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' });
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - ShipHours">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground mb-8"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-4 w-4">
          <path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"></path>
          <path d="M19 12H5"></path>
        </svg>
        Back
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-8">
        Last updated: {currentDate}
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            ShipHours values the privacy of its users. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
            use, store, and protect your personal information when you use our time tracking service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We collect the following types of information:
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">2.1 Account Information</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Name and email address (when you create an account)</li>
            <li>Profile photo (if provided through social login)</li>
            <li>Account preferences and settings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">2.2 Work Session Data</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Logged work sessions (date, task, duration)</li>
            <li>Weekly hour goals you set</li>
            <li>Activity history and progress</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">2.3 Technical Data</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>IP address and browser type</li>
            <li>Operating system and device type</li>
            <li>Pages visited and usage time</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We use your information to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Provide and maintain the ShipHours service</li>
            <li>Personalize your experience and display your progress</li>
            <li>Generate statistics and dashboards for your work sessions</li>
            <li>Send goal notifications (if enabled)</li>
            <li>Improve our service and develop new features</li>
            <li>Communicate important updates about the service</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Storage and Security</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Your data is stored on secure servers. We implement technical and organizational
            security measures to protect your information against unauthorized access, alteration,
            disclosure, or destruction. This includes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Data encryption in transit (HTTPS)</li>
            <li>Passwords stored with secure hashing</li>
            <li>Restricted access to user data</li>
            <li>Regular data backups</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
            We may share data only in the following situations:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>With your explicit consent</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
            <li>To protect our rights and safety</li>
            <li>With service providers who assist us (hosting, analytics)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            You have the following rights regarding your data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Export your data in a readable format</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Limit the processing of your data</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">
            To exercise these rights, access your account settings or contact us.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We use cookies and similar technologies to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Keep you signed in to your account</li>
            <li>Remember your preferences (theme, settings)</li>
            <li>Understand how you use the service</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">
            You can configure your browser to refuse cookies, but this may affect service functionality.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">8. Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We retain your data while your account is active or as needed to provide the service.
            If you delete your account, we will remove your personal data within 30 days,
            except where retention is required for legal purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Minors</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            ShipHours is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information
            from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us
            with information, please contact us so we can remove that data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of significant
            changes through the application or by email. We recommend reviewing this page regularly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data,
            please contact us through the application settings.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border">
        <a
          href="/terms"
          class="text-primary hover:underline"
        >
          View Terms of Use
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
